      <section id="section_All-Flash-Array_JBOF_Application_0jnm7ya6b" class="- topic/section " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="section:1;39:35">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="title:2;42:32">All-Flash-Array/JBOF Application</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:3;45:24">Switchtec can be used as a fanout switch in an all-flash-array or just-a-bunch-of-flash (JBOF) application. Native support for PCIe surprise-plug and interoperability with OpenBMC makes building all-flash-array applications simple and straightforward. Switchtec dynamic bifurcation allows for multi-module carriers which allows a single x4 U.2 to be dynamically replaced with a U.2 carrier that contains, for example, dual x2 M.2 modules without requiring a device reset. Higher bandwidth upstream links at x16 Gen4 allow for even more downstream Endpoints providing low latency, high capacity, fanout storage. Switchtec features NVMe-MI enclosure management which is accessible in-band or via SMBUS. </p>
         <fig id="fig_Single_host_connectivity_to_x2_and_x4_SS_6ieugwk1e" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="fig:1;49:28">
