         </fig>
      </section>
      <section id="section_Active_Passive_fail-over_Application_1jnm7ya6b" class="- topic/section " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="section:2;65:35">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="title:4;68:32">Active/Passive fail-over Application</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:4;71:24">The simple all-flash-array can be extended with no hardware changes to support an active/passive fail-over by using open-source Switchtec drivers to provide a host to host tunnel to provide health information between the backup host and the primary. When the backup host fails to contact the primary, it can issue commands to the switch via the management Endpoint and facilitate the addition/removal of PCIe Endpoints into its own domain. This fail-over mechanism utilizes a feature called <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="i:1;73:27">dynamic partitioning</i> which is available on the entire family of Switchtec devices. PCIe Endpoints added to the backup host appear as PCIe hot-adds and no host reboot is required to access them.</p>
         <fig id="fig_Single_host_cascaded_SSD_connectivity_1ieugwk1e" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="fig:2;77:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="title:5;80:35">Active/Passive fail-over example</title>
