         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:5;99:24">For systems that require a higher level of availability, Switchtec can be implemented in a dual host, dual switch, and dual-ported drive application where a host, switch, or drive port failure does not impact the system operation. To extend the high availability application, Switchtec also supports Cache Mirroring which provides real-time replication of data from one host during I/O operations to the backup host. This guarantees that the backup host is cache coherent with the primary and can execute a truly non-disruptive fail-over.</p>
         <fig id="fig_Dual_host_SSD_application_3ieugwk1e" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="fig:3;103:28">
