         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:7;151:24">For virtual machine environments that scale, the bare metal requirements to support VMs needs to be as decomposable as the software in order to allow for hardware to scale with the requirements of the VMs. A management CPU can be used to compose a node in hardware consisting of compute, storage, graphics, and network by issuing dynamic partitioning commands to Switchtec. The switch simply binds the appropriate components to a PCIe domain and then presents it to the node which can, in turn, build out virtual machines.</p>
