      <section id="section_Automotive_GPU_Application_6jnm7ya6b" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="section:6;170:41">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="title:12;173:33">Automotive/GPU Application</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:8;176:32">With increasing compute and machine vision, PCIe is becoming a de-facto standard within the vehicle. Switchtec provides a flexible, fault tolerant solution which ties together traditional infotainment systems with cutting edge AI-based machine vision camera systems, custom FPGAs for processing LIDAR and ultrasound sensors, and low latency NVMe storage. Switchtec's dynamic partitioning feature is perfectly suited to provide fault tolerance to the Automotive Driver Assistance System (ADAS) where the backup (in-car CPU) can act as a failover for the main CPU. Switchtec’s NT Multicasting feature enables any host CPU to broadcast data simultaneously to multiple <ph status="deleted" rev="deltaxml-delete" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="ph:1;176:740">end-points</ph>
            <ph status="new" rev="deltaxml-add" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="ph:2;177:49">Endpoints</ph> in the multi-host system and any EP can also send data simultaneously to multiple hosts in the system. Switchtec’s multicast capability helps save bandwidth utilization at the source and reduces overall memory bandwidth usage to improve automotive system performance in an action-reaction situation.</p>
         <fig id="fig_Automotive_GPU_Application_7jnm7ya6b" class="- topic/fig " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="fig:6;182:34">
