      <section id="section_Drive_Slicing_Application_ajnm7ya6b" class="- topic/section " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="section:8;227:35">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="title:16;230:33">Drive Slicing Application</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:10;233:25">With the introduction of Single-Root I/O Virtualization (SRIOV) devices such as NVMe SSDs, Switchtec PAX can be extended to support a concept known as <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="i:2;235:27">drive slicing</i>. This concept is centered around the concept of multiple hosts being able to access the same NVMe device simultaneously and slicing the storage in the device. This is achieved by SRIOV capable NVMe storage devices resenting multiple virtual functions which have the same core characteristics as the physical function. PAX takes a single multi-function SRIOV Endpoint and presents each virtual function as a single function NVMe Endpoint to each host. In the example below, there are six Endpoints each connected to a PAX switch in a PCIe fabric. Switchtec PAX presents each virtual function of he SRIOV Endpoint as a single physical function NVMe Endpoint. Each host sees a <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="i:3;237:27">slice</i> of each Endpoint as if it is a unique dedicated drive. </p>
         <fig id="fig_Drive_Slicing_Application_bjnm7ya6b" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="fig:8;241:28">
