         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\COMMON\Appnotes\Application_Examples\trident_application_examples.xml" xtrc="p:12;292:25">Switchtec enables inter-domain communication between multiple host systems. Using Switchtec’s virtual switch partitioning and NTB capabilities, each host is connected via non-transparent Endpoints (NT EP) to a separate virtual switch partition. This configuration allows any host connection to be reset, reconfigured and hot-plugged without operational impact the other host systems. Large PCIe topologies can be built with NTB within switches and NT Crosslink between switches. These types of topologies are also favoured in automotive applications where automotive subsystems need to be isolated from each other to prevent error propagation.</p>
